  We can only change the status of an account when we receive the fully executed agreement from ORS   n Changes to Award Status Q  The sponsor granted a no cost extension  Contracts  GCO t Banner reflect the new end date  A  Changes to the terms of an award must flow through Office of Research Services  ORS  for approval and processing first  GCO will update the grant end date and other relevant grant records  You may wish to notify GCO that an extension is pending  as a courtesy Q  My grant is in anticipation status A  No  We can only change the status of an account when we receive the fully executed agreement from ORS    n nReporting n n nQ  Who is responsible for financial reporting to sponsors  nA  The Office of Grants   Contracts  GCO  is responsible for submitting financial status reports  a k a  grant expenditure reports or grant budget reports  to the sponsor  the sponsor requires that the report be signed by an official University representative  which is GCO  the Grant Specialist to whom the grant is assigned will send a copy of the report to the respective department  s business manager for their records  nQ  What am I supposed to do when I receive a Report of Expenditures  ROE  from GCO  nA  The ROE is a reflection of the grant activity as posted to Banner  issuing a final bill  or closing a grant out     days of receipt with your changes or your approval  nThe ROE points to specific actions you need to take in the fulfillment of your administrative duties  nQ  What is an Interim Financial Status Report  nA  An Interim Financial Status Report is a financial report that is submitted at specific intervals during the course of the project  as prescribed by the terms and conditions of the award  semi annual  or annual SF      SF      or SF      nSome grants do not require interim financial reports SNAP  They only require an SF     filed at the conclusion of the project period  nQ  What am I supposed to do when the FSR for my Federal grant shows an unobligated balance  nA  It depends on the terms and conditions of the grant  nIf the grant is NOT under expanded authorities  the PI must request the agency  s approval to carry the balance forward to the next budget period and provide a budget to that end  Meanwhile GCO will restrict the balance pending the agency  s approval  at which time it will be released for use  nIf the grant IS under expanded authorities  the unobligated balance can automatically be carried forward to the next budget period in as much as   % of the current year award  nIf the grant is under SNAP  the unobligated balance can automatically be carried forward to the renewal segment GMO  may only allow a partial carryover if  in their view  the full unobligated balance is not necessary to complete the project  the agency would issue a notice of award to that effect and GCO would restrict the unobligated balance accordingly  nQ  What is "Expanded Authorities"  nA  This is a privilege granted by a Federal agency  whereby the agency delegates some of its prior approval functions to a grantee institution  the agency confers to the grantee the authority  nto incur pre award costs nto carry forward unobligated balances nto rebudget  within certain limits  nto extend the final budget year of a project  one time  nQ  How do I know if my award is under expanded authorities  nA  Most awards from the following Federal agencies are under expanded authorities  AFOSR  ARO  AMRMC  DOE  EPA  NASA  NIH  NSF  ONR  and USDA  Please see the terms   conditions in your award document to confirm the status of your award  nQ  My Federal contract just expired SF      required  nA  No      only grants and cooperative agreements have this requirement  n Reporting Q  Who is responsible for financial reporting to sponsors  A  The Office of Grants   Contracts  GCO  is responsible for submitting financial status reports  a k a  grant expenditure reports or grant budget reports  to the sponsor  the sponsor requires that the report be signed by an official University representative  which is GCO  the Grant Specialist to whom the grant is assigned will send a copy of the report to the respective department s business manager for their records Q  What am I supposed to do when I receive a Report of Expenditures  ROE  from GCO  A  The ROE is a reflection of the grant activity as posted to Banner  issuing a final bill  or closing a grant out     days of receipt with your changes or your approval The ROE points to specific actions you need to take in the fulfillment of your administrative duties Q  What is an Interim Financial Status Report  A  An Interim Financial Status Report is a financial report that is submitted at specific intervals during the course of the project  as prescribed by the terms and conditions of the award  semi annual  or annual SF      SF      or SF     Some grants do not require interim financial reports SNAP  They only require an SF     filed at the conclusion of the project period Q  What am I supposed to do when the FSR for my Federal grant shows an unobligated balance  A  It depends on the terms and conditions of the grant If the grant is NOT under expanded authorities  the PI must request the agency s approval to carry the balance forward to the next budget period and provide a budget to that end  Meanwhile GCO will restrict the balance pending the agency s approval  at which time it will be released for use If the grant IS under expanded authorities  the unobligated balance can automatically be carried forward to the next budget period in as much as   % of the current year award If the grant is under SNAP  the unobligated balance can automatically be carried forward to the renewal segment GMO  may only allow a partial carryover if  in their view  the full unobligated balance is not necessary to complete the project  the agency would issue a notice of award to that effect and GCO would restrict the unobligated balance accordingly Q  What is "Expanded Authorities"  A  This is a privilege granted by a Federal agency  whereby the agency delegates some of its prior approval functions to a grantee institution  the agency confers to the grantee the authority  Q  How do I know if my award is under expanded authorities  A  Most awards from the following Federal agencies are under expanded authorities  AFOSR  ARO  AMRMC  DOE  EPA  NASA  NIH  NSF  ONR  and USDA  Please see the terms   conditions in your award document to confirm the status of your award Q  My Federal contract just expired SF      required  A  No      only grants and cooperative agreements have this requirement  n n nPost Award n n n Post Award Federal A     Audit Reports Effort Reporting Essentials of Post Award Administration Contact ORS or GCO  Contact GCO Staff The Award Life Cycle Roles   Responsibilities Preparing to Receive an Award Receiving an Award Managing an Award Closing Out an Award Training Resources Indirect Cost Rates  F A Monitoring Expenditures OMB Uniform Guidance Sponsored Project Expenditures Links   Resources Forms Policies and Procedures Glossary Job Aids and Training Materials UIC Frequently Asked Questions Who To Ask Who To Ask  Types of Questions UIC Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research OVCR Main Office     Administrative Office Building  AOB  nMC     n     West Polk Street nChicago  IL       T               F                novcrweb uic edu Send Us a Message Offices Units ORS Office of Research Services OPRS Office for the Protection of Research Subjects COI Conflict of Commitment   Interest OACIB Office of Animal Care   Institutional Biosafety RDS Research Development Services CTO Clinical Trials RRC Research Resources Center BRL Biologic Resources Laboratory GCO Grants and Contracts  Having problems accessing this site  Please contact the webmaster    Privacy Policy webmaster Privacy Policy CookieSettings 